primary_outcome.description:
Likert score ratings of image quality for Blue Light Imaging (BLI), Blue Light Imaging-bright (BLI-brt) and Flexible spectral-Imaging Color Enhancement (FICE) images. Each BLI and BLI-Brt setting was compared to FICE, to determine which settings were equivalent to FICE.
Likert Score Scale:
Not seen;
poor but usable, characteristic features are detectable but details are not fully reproduced; features just visible;
good; allows an adequate assessment, details of anatomical structures are visible but not necessarily clearly defined; details emerging;
very good; allows an excellent assessment, anatomical details are clearly defined; details clear
This was a blinded and randomized Reader assessment of all BLI and FICE images.

